<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="G" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Grapple2" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Grapple,</orth> vb. 1) intr. to wrestle, to contend in close fight: <bibl n="shak. lll 2.218" default="NO" valid="yes">LLL II, 218</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 3.1.104" default="NO" valid="yes">John III, 1, 104</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 5.1.61" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 61</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 1.3.197" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A I, 3, 197</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 1.1.257" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B I, 1, 257</bibl>.<lb />2) tr. to clasp: <cit><quote>and g. thee unto a pagan shore,</quote> <bibl n="shak. jn 5.2.36" default="NO" valid="yes">John V, 2, 36</bibl></cit> (O. Edd. <emph>cripple</emph>). <cit><quote>g. your minds to sternage of this navy,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl></cit> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.0" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III Chor.</bibl> <emph>--s you to the</emph> <cit><quote>heart and love of us,</quote> <bibl n="shak. mac 3.1.106" default="NO" valid="yes">Mcb. III, 1, 106</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>g. them to thy soul with hoops of steel,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ham 1.3.63" default="NO" valid="yes">Hml. I, 3, 63</bibl></cit>.
<pb n="492" />
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>